in other places.

8D83E5A90EB04635AB036956BA77251B.description:
Perform routine events
and use familiar objects
in appropriate ways
(carry clean
diaper to changing
table, talk on phone,
“water” plants with
pitcher).

886EFB335821440989B88A5A4DDAB23D.description:
Notice a change in
familiar objects, places,
or events (frown at
family member with
a new haircut, look
for furniture that was
moved).

64063B52060F42AEAF944CBCAC17F482.description:
Search in several
places where an object
has been hidden
recently.

3736416059144FA2AC459B1E9F734411.description:
Observe and imitate sounds,
movements, and facial
expressions, including things
they have seen in the past or
in other places.

9E1AA11A7E9B4A86868FAC9E8DFF5DFC.description:
Repeat an action to make
something happen again
(make sounds when music
stops, bounce up and down to
get adult to continue “horsey
ride”).

CE8303DC128746EB9E834D67C3151FF2.description:
Anticipate routine events
(smile, wave arms and legs,
move toward adult holding
bottle).

D444D7D3095549C9863F40F7B967ADF9.description:
Respond differently to
familiar vs. unfamiliar people,
objects, and situations (reach
for new interesting toy instead
of old familiar toy; move
toward familiar caregiver
but hide head on a family
member’s shoulder when new
person comes near).

9ADC7C68182C4A9D95A24D6331D6988D.description:
Search for objects that are
hidden or partly hidden.

8E7E7D2B66B5469BA3FC5FFA626D9BD5.description: Children recall information and use it for addressing new situations and problems.

9BFB09F01F034EBB837D3C8B2A3A4CA1.description:
Organize and use
information through matching,
grouping, and sequencing.

25BFA46CAD2F4C4FA996D4FFBF98226F.description:
Distinguish appearance from
reality (the person behind a
mask is still the same person;
recognize that a fantasy story
could not be real).

271E923C098C4B86A00CD0AB6D67666D.description:
Express knowledge
gathered with their senses
using play, various art forms,
language, and other forms
of representation. (Show an
understanding that one block
is heavier than another, that
play dough can be modeled
into longer and shorter logs,
that blocks can be used to
represent a telephone).

937A010DEF284B7C861734D773845C70.description:
Explore objects, tools, and materials systematically to learn about their properties (weigh an object, observe
something from the top of the
object to the bottom).

25E273E86A5D4A7DBAE66DF3286BAFD4.description:
Group familiar objects that
go together (shoe and sock,
brush and paint, hammer and
nail).

40AC12F8AFF2444BB570964002A84D17.description:
Enjoy fantasy and makebelieve and can sometimes
distinguish appearance from
reality (the person behind
the mask remains the same
person).

82FFC6BEDEB348E686BEC377B5E43444.description:
Express knowledge
gathered with their senses
using play, various art forms,
language, and other forms
of representation. (Show an
understanding that one block
is heavier than another, that
play dough can be modeled
into longer and shorter logs,
that blocks can be used to
represent a telephone).

D7071B9CD71340448A6DB4AD87EA5E09.description:
Explore objects, tools, and materials systematically to learn about their properties (weigh an object, observe
something from the top of the
object to the bottom).

2D5B21DB597246729CCFB80DEF0D5DDD.description:
Express knowledge
gathered with their
senses through play
(imitate something they
have seen an adult do,
show they understand
how to sort by sorting
toys as they are
playing).

9514F3046AA94CDBB9D5B94DF99F4B54.description:
Experiment with safe
tools to learn how they
work (wooden hammer
with pegs, sifter,
funnel).

FED61E9045BE4104841B9926C7B7AA10.description:
Explore objects and
materials physically
to learn about their
properties.

20412E209FCC4B248192524F97D91AAE.description:
Explore space with
their bodies (fit self
into large box, crawl
under table, climb
over low walls).

2979A1E56F4A4A0A836D38C767AE051F.description:
Actively explore
objects by handling
them in many ways
(moving, carrying,
filling, dumping,
smelling, and putting
in mouth).

253964BA79C24E20B8B5E780530126B2.description:
Turn head or move
toward sounds.

06C11C1CD44A462A978EB386D47AD01B.description:
Discover different
shapes, sizes and
textures by
exploring (put toys
in mouth, crawl
over pillows, pick
up large objects).

C9DD75F3D06B49D09B7359A00419346B.description: Children use their senses to construct knowledge about the world around them.
